  "flat-roof-repair-jacksonville": {
    title: "Flat Roofing Contractor: Why Flat Roofs Leak More Than Shingles",
    metaTitle: "Jacksonville Flat Roofing Contractor | Repair & Installation Guide",
    excerpt: "Flat roofs are tricky. Find out why you need a specialized flat roofing contractor for your Florida home and the best materials to use.",
    content: `
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">If you have a porch, a garage extension, a modern home addition, or a commercial building, you probably have a flat roof somewhere. And if you've owned it long enough, you've probably dealt with a leak.</p>

      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Here's the truth: flat roofs aren't actually flat. They have a slight slope to drain water. But compared to a pitched shingle roof, they're much more likely to develop problems if not installed and maintained correctly. That's why you need a <strong>flat roofing contractor</strong> who understands the specialized membranes and techniques required.</p>

      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Need a <a href="/services/commercial-roofing" class="text-primary hover:underline font-semibold">specialized commercial flat roofing</a> solution for your business? We handle both residential and commercial flat roof projects.</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-secondary mt-10 mb-4">Why Flat Roofs Are Different</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">On a steep shingle roof, gravity does most of the work. Water runs off before it can cause problems. On a flat roof, water sits. It pools. It finds every tiny imperfection and exploits it.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">People often ask, "<strong>What does a roofing contractor do</strong> differently for a flat roof vs. a sloped one?" The answer is: everything. Different materials, different installation techniques, different maintenance requirements.</p>

      <div class="bg-primary/10 border-l-4 border-primary p-6 my-8 rounded-r-lg">
        <p class="font-bold text-secondary mb-2">Gimo's Take:</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">"I see it all the time: someone gets a cheap price on a flat roof repair, and six months later, the same spot is leaking again. Flat roofs require specialized knowledge. If your contractor mainly does shingles and treats flat roofing as a side job, you're asking for trouble."</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-secondary mt-10 mb-4">Common Causes of Flat Roof Leaks</h2>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-secondary mt-6 mb-2">1. Ponding Water</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">If water sits on your roof for more than 48 hours after rain, you have a ponding problem. This accelerates membrane deterioration and eventually finds a way inside.</p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-secondary mt-6 mb-2">2. Membrane Damage</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Florida's UV exposure is brutal. Over time, it breaks down roofing membranes, causing cracks and splits. Add in foot traffic from HVAC maintenance, and you have wear points.</p>

